# LLM Provider Configuration

# ========== HUGGING FACE (Cloud-based; uses your HF credits) ==========
# 1. Create access token: https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens
# 2. Uncomment and set token/model
# 3. Run: TRAINING_AGENT_MODE=llm LLM_PROVIDER=huggingface python train.py
#
# Notes:
# - Use HF_TOKEN (preferred) or HUGGINGFACE_API_KEY
# - HUGGINGFACE_MODEL must be an inference-enabled chat model
#
# LLM_PROVIDER=huggingface
# HF_TOKEN=hf_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# HUGGINGFACE_MODEL=meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct
# HUGGINGFACE_BASE_URL=https://router.huggingface.co/v1

# ========== OPENROUTER (Cloud-based) ==========
# Use this for cloud-based LLM without local Ollama installation
# 1. Get API key from https://openrouter.ai
# 2. Uncomment and set your API key below
# 3. Run: TRAINING_AGENT_MODE=llm LLM_PROVIDER=openrouter python train.py

# LLM_PROVIDER=openrouter
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
# OPENROUTER_MODEL=openai/gpt-3.5-turbo

# Available OpenRouter models (examples):
# - openai/gpt-4                          (Most capable, expensive)
# - openai/gpt-3.5-turbo                  (Fast, cheaper)
# - meta-llama/llama-2-70b               (Open source)
# - mistralai/mistral-7b                  (Fast, open source)
# - anthropic/claude-3-sonnet             (Balanced)


# ========== OLLAMA (Local) ==========
# Use this to run LLM on your local machine
# 1. Install Ollama from https://ollama.ai
# 2. Run: ollama pull mistral
# 3. Uncomment lines below and run: ollama serve
# 4. Run: TRAINING_AGENT_MODE=llm LLM_PROVIDER=ollama python train.py

# LLM_PROVIDER=ollama
# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
# OLLAMA_MODEL=mistral


# ========== GROQ (Fast Cloud API) ==========
# Use this for super-fast inference with open source models
# 1. Get API key from https://console.groq.com
# 2. Uncomment and set your API key below
# 3. Run: TRAINING_AGENT_MODE=llm LLM_PROVIDER=groq python train.py

# LLM_PROVIDER=groq
# GROQ_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
# GROQ_MODEL=mixtral-8x7b-32768


# ========== RL TRAINING (No LLM, uses Q-learning) ==========
# Use this for faster training without LLM API calls
# Run: TRAINING_AGENT_MODE=rl python train.py

# TRAINING_AGENT_MODE=rl

# ========== MODES & SWEEP ==========
# Supported modes:
# TRAINING_AGENT_MODE=llm
# TRAINING_AGENT_MODE=rl
# TRAINING_AGENT_MODE=hybrid
#
# Optional quick check for all 3 modes:
# RUN_MODE_SWEEP=true
# MODE_SWEEP_EPISODES=6
